<TITLE> Dhaka clubs decline player transfers before BFF poll </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 12 (bdnews24.com) Dhaka clubs Wednesday declined to take part in the inter-club footballer transfers and play the Independence Cup Football Tournament before the Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) election. The refusal came through a written statement signed by the high-ups of professional league clubs Abahani Limited, Mohammedan SC, Muktijoddha Sangsad, Sheikh Russel KC, Brothers Union, Arambagh KS, Farashganj SC and Rahmatganj MFS. They placed their demand with Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) president SA Sultan Wednesday. They questioned wanted to know how it would be possible to play the Independence Cup and participate in the players' bourse simultaneously. The footballer transfers are to start on March 15 and continue until the start of the second edition B. League. They also said it was not possible to take part in the player transfers before the BFF poll, scheduled for April 28. They also blamed the BFF for not taking enough initiatives to make the Independence Cup gorgeous with even the football governing body showing reluctance to hold the meet earlier. The club officials said that they were not against playing the Independence Cup, but that they might be faced with technical difficulties during the player transfers. They also said that the BFF announced a yearly calendar hurriedly that might confuse the football-loving people as it had no timeframe along with the confirmation of the sponsorships for the tournaments. They also said that they wanted to play football and were determined to bring dynamism to football. "We think it will be rational to start the activities of the player transfers after the BFF poll and there will be assurance and acceptance of the new committee's plans," said the statement. 
